= display_search_boxes('articles')

.row
  .landing_main.col-sm-8

    .title Articles+

    = render partial: '/datasource_warning', locals: {warning: warning}


    %p Searches a large database of mostly full-text journals, encyclopedia and newspaper articles; this database also includes e-books and government documents.

    %p Newspaper articles are excluded from the initial search results. To include them, click the 'x' next to "Not Content Type: Newspaper Articles" above the search results.


    %p Other useful databases for scholarly articles in the:
    %ul
      %li Humanities and Social Sciences, try #{link_to 'Ebscohost Research Databases', 'https://resolver.library.columbia.edu/clio6329559'} or #{link_to 'ProQuest', 'https://resolver.library.columbia.edu/clio8557099'}
      %li Sciences, try #{link_to 'Web of Science', 'https://resolver.library.columbia.edu/clio2054244'} or #{link_to 'Scopus', 'https://resolver.library.columbia.edu/clio6273999'}
      %li 18<sup>th</sup> and 19<sup>th</sup> centuries, try #{link_to 'American Periodicals', 'https://resolver.library.columbia.edu/ARS2786'} or #{link_to 'British Periodicals', 'https://resolver.library.columbia.edu/clio6022732'}


    %p To find articles in a specific newspaper or published in a specific city:
    %ul
      %li For US newspapers from the 1990s on: #{link_to 'ProQuest', 'https://resolver.library.columbia.edu/clio6270029'}
      %li For US newspapers before 1990s: #{link_to 'ProQuest Historial Newspapers', 'https://resolver.library.columbia.edu/AUN8518'} and #{link_to "America's Historical Newspapers", 'https://resolver.library.columbia.edu/clio4403555'}
      %li For international newspapers: #{link_to 'Factiva', 'https://resolver.library.columbia.edu/AUQ3920'}


    %p Use #{datasource_switch_link('Databases', 'databases')} to browse all of our databases by subject.

    %p To see a list of resources by subject, consult our #{link_to 'subject guides', 'https://library.columbia.edu/services/subject-guides.html'}.


